links.displaytext: Part Two:  The Field Placement Process
Using Our Opportunity (Opps) List:    Four Step Process
Step #4 Tell Us What You Thought
All students are successful in getting a placement that they have selected, whether they search in the first or second phase.
How to Help Process Go Smoothly
A Few Words About  Your Approach
Alternate Ways To Obtain A Placement

slidetranscripts.Text:
Many partners

Three MSW programs in the Twin Cities we have all agreed to follow the same time line and the same overall process. You have a window of time when you can interview at agencies.

Includes interviewing, making choices, and placement.

Consider which settings feel like a good match, for your interests, skills, learning objectives and learning style.

Tell us your preferences, and we use that in determining each match.
Explain each.

Be realistic could you use some extra support? Career development, disabilities services??

Can you do these hours?

Do you feel the style of supervision and the learning environment will work for you?\

Challenge your self where can YOU get new learning?

This is a time to try things out, that can inform the rest of your careers.

Every placement offers SO much to learn!

YOU WILL FIND A PLACEMENT

This is a collaborative process:

You are responsible for following the instructions and using the information you are given, for following through, and for how you present in your written materials and during interviews.

We are responsible for developing partnerships with agencies, giving you and them good information, and for continuing to support you throughout every step of the process.

Most students are placed as a result of the spring interviewing process, which youll be learning about shortly.

Students who cannot be here during the spring, or for students who didnt find the right match at that time, we work together during the summer, until everyone is placed.

The practicum experience is where you learn transferable skills. It offers exposure to the role of the social worker across settings. It is not an irreversible choice about specialization.

Today youre going to learn about what you can do to help the process be successful, and as smooth as possible.
A word about Canvas site available Saturday afternoon by 2 pm

Opps list on Canvas.

Agencies we have developed relationships with they are eager to meet you.
(Tips for reading agency description next.)

Show them what to look for on sample (handout)

Inside cover

Hyper linked index

Appendix A, including last page to sign and turn in

PROPRIETARY INFORMATION =- DO NOT RELEASE TO OTHERS, OR SHARE WITH FRIENDS FROM OTHER PROGRAMS.

Some agencies only work with us.

St. Cloud story.

Look at Sample handout

Foundation v. Clinical critical that you keep track of this we do not

Who contacts who? May want to be sure you have a mix.

Group interviews VERY important.

Grid important info.

Working with our class schedules 682, etc.

Field is a full year course, methods is a full year course.

Mileage if required to use your car we assume mileage is reimbursed.

Appendix A in sample Opps List more

$$ - a few offer stipends, many offer mileage reimbursement, may incur cost for parking, agency may be billing for services. HENNEPIN COUNTY

Online applications

Do not go back to same agency!!!

Try something new!

Look at sample in Sample Opps List.

Consider this informed consent.

No fewer than 6, no more than 10 DO NOT NEED TO DO 10!!!!!!!

Be realistic and be open minded

You may not get interview at every place. Mix agency contact student/student contact agency.

Include agencies that are not accepting paper applications.

MUST BE FACE to FACE

Field coordinator is not always the field instructor

May have more than one interview at agency

Do NOT CALL before time frame

Dont put off calling agencies

If cant make group meeting, call to see if other arrangements possible

Go prepared: Agencies tell us they appreciate how well prepared our students are.

Review info on agency in opps and check online.

Have questions for them as well. Ask about safety, mileage, parking fees.

Be professional: timely, neat, courteous. Call well in advance if must cancel.

This is first impression of you and our program and fellow students. - Update your message on cell phone.

You arrive with capital from the good behaviors of others. Build on it!

Most importantly: Dont finalize dont believe them if they offer it to you, dont feel pressured to accept/reject. Instead: thank them, be positive, indicate the process continues.

Be realistic and open minded

You will learn in every setting. Think about what each setting has to offer you in your professional development.

While you must choose and order agencies adding notes can help me (like: I cant decide between these two either would be fine)

Matches based on what is possible.

You are setting the terms of what is possible.

Second phase search additional students, some new agencies, opportunity to try agencies you didnt try the first time.

Will effect anywhere from 1 to 40 of you.

See handout for all of these also I will go over here.

12-month MPSI;

See handout for all of these

Will effect anywhere from 1 to 40 of you.

Field directors job is to support you through process.

Hold onto instructions and review.

UST EMAIL ONLY!!!!!!!!!!!!

Make a schedule

Follow the timeline and due dates

Dont put it off

One step at a time

It WILL all get done

You are the beneficiaries of our great reputation, and the stewards of it.

We appreciate the quality of your students

We interviewed five of your students and wanted them all. They were SO professional.

The caliber of students is really impressive.

Bad outcomes: dressing casually, chewing gum, sitting cross-legged in a chair during an interview; overestimating your skill; not following up in a timely manner.

Personal dynamics strengths, vulnerabilities, fast pace, learning style, disabilities, background issues

Presentation proofread your work.

Positive outlook glitches, rumors, flexibility

Quote from me from NASW news March 2015: Field placement is the beginning of the journey. Nothing is ever wasted all of it becomes part of your development, your professional identity, and your sense of what works and what doesnt work. There are many layers of learning in field.

Positive support of friends, peers, field faculty, advisor

You are likely to feel very anxious in the first week

You are likely to feel panicked in the second week.

I loved the process! I liked getting out into the community and seeing what programs were available, and also to practice my interviewing skills!

It was a whirlwind, but exciting to see and learn about different agencies in the Twin Cities. It was definitely a valuable learning experience.

It has been an incredible learning experience. I loved all the places and opportunities where I interviewed.
Start with alternatives, then do Opps List

DO NOT contact any agency before you have approval from me.

You can choose this option later as well.

UNDER CERTAIN CONDITIONS

Role issues Protect you in the role of learner. This is your time to learn!!!

Consider carefully: sometimes dont get oriented as well; may be harder to advocate for learning needs.

Note that it is 2019

Range of places, some unique to SB

Must be able to accommodate a full-time schedule

Sequential learning learn theory, then apply.

Must take corresponding Theory/Methods course first

Will still be in seminar in summer. Can still consider a self-initiated placement.

Graduation either period.

Just because we offer these options does not mean your particular situation can be approved.

Must meet our criteria

Must be a good enough setting for your learning.

For instance, cannot repeat agency, cannot repeat block format

PROTECT you as a learner

PROTECT your investment in your education.
